<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Irina Shayk commanded attention in a figure-hugging dress on Thursday afternoon, as she turned the sidewalk into her personal runway in New York City. </p>

<p>On her laid-back strut, the Vogue cover girl showcased her model physique in a cobalt blue motorsport-inspired minidress with a top-to-bottom zipper down the front.  </p>

<p>With her toned legs on full display, the thigh-skimming outfit guaranteed Irina, 34, plenty of attention from onlookers during her latest strut around the Big Apple. </p>

<p>Leggy display: Irina Shayk commanded attention in a figure-hugging dress on Thursday afternoon, as she turned the sidewalk into her personal runway on in New York City</p>

<p>She accentuated her leggy frame with a pair of black leather booties, which hit her tan and muscular calves. </p>

<p>The bombshell oozed confidence, as she accessorized her ensemble with a tiny yellow purse and a few delicate chains around her neck. </p>

<p>While the Russian beauty opted not to wear a CDC-recommended mask, she completed her look with a pair of large hoop earrings and tiny black sunglasses.  </p>

<p>Curves: On her impromptu strut, the Vogue cover girl showcased her model physique in a cobalt blue minidress with a top-to-bottom zipper down the front</p>

<p>Irina did not appear to be joined by her three-year-old daughter Lea, whom she shares with her ex-boyfriend Bradley Cooper. </p>

<p>The couple split after four years together last year, and have been co-parenting their little one together ever since.</p>

<p>Bradley recently revealed he had been teaching their daughter how to swim in his bathtub, while caring for his mother Gloria Campano at home. </p>

<p>Strutting around: With her toned legs on full display, the thigh-skimming outfit guaranteed Irina, 34, plenty of attention from onlookers during her latest strut around the Big Apple</p>

<p>'I'm with my daughter and my mother and my two dogs, and we have not left the house,' he said in a discussion with Interview Magazine.</p>

<p>She added: 'My mother is going to be 80, and she has a colostomy bag, so I can't let anybody in the house. And I can't leave the house, because if she gets it, it's over.'</p>

<p>'We live in a little townhouse, thankfully there's a backyard. I'm running a one-man preschool. We get up, we do swim class in the bathtub.' </p>

